{"title_page": "1992 United States presidential election in North Dakota", "text_new": "{{main|1992 United States presidential election}}\n{{Infobox Election\n| election_name = 1992 [[United States presidential election]] in North Dakota\n| country = North Dakota\n| type = presidential\n| ongoing = no\n| previous_election = 1988 United States presidential election in North Dakota\n| previous_year = 1988\n| next_election = 1996 United States presidential election in North Dakota\n| next_year = 1996\n| election_date = November 3, 1992\n| image_size = x160px\n| image1 = George H. W. Bush presidential portrait (cropped 2).jpg\n| nominee1 = '''[[George H.W. Bush]]''' \n| party1 = Republican Party (United States)\n| home_state1 = [[Texas]]\n| running_mate1 = '''[[Dan Quayle]]'''\n| electoral_vote1 = '''3'''\n| popular_vote1 = '''136,244'''\n| percentage1 = '''44.22%'''\t\n| image2 = Bill Clinton.jpg\n| nominee2 = [[Bill Clinton]]\n| party2 = Democratic Party (United States)\n| home_state2 = [[Arkansas]]\n| running_mate2 = [[Al Gore]]\n| electoral_vote2 = 0\n| popular_vote2 = 99,168\n| percentage2 = 32.18%\t\n| image3 = RossPerotColor.jpg\n| nominee3 = [[Ross Perot]]\n| party3 = Independent (politician)\n| home_state3 = [[Texas]]\n| running_mate3 = [[James Stockdale]]\n| electoral_vote3 = 0\n| popular_vote3 = 71,084\t\n| percentage3 = 23.07%\n| map_image = ND1992.jpg\n| map_size = 400px\n| map_caption = County Results\n{{col-start}}\n{{col-2}}\n'''Bush'''\n{{legend|#ffccd0|30\u201340%}}\n{{legend|#f2b3be|40\u201350%}}\n{{legend|#e27f90|50\u201360%}}\n{{col-2}}\n'''Clinton'''\n{{legend|#d3e7ff|30\u201340%}}\n{{legend|#b9d7ff|40\u201350%}}\n{{legend|#86b6f2|50\u201360%}}\n{{col-end}}\n| title = President\n| before_election = [[George H. W. Bush]]\n| before_party = Republican Party (United States)\n| after_election = [[Bill Clinton]]\n| after_party = Democratic Party (United States)\n}}\n{{ElectionsND}}\n\nThe '''1992 United States presidential election in North Dakota''' took place on November 3, 1992, as part of the [[1992 United States presidential election]]. Voters chose three representatives, or electors to the [[United States Electoral College|Electoral College]], who voted for [[President of the United States|president]] and [[Vice President of the United States|vice president]].\n\n[[North Dakota]] was won by incumbent President [[George H. W. Bush]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|R]]-[[Texas]]) with 44.22% of the popular vote over [[List of governors of Arkansas|Governor]] [[Bill Clinton]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|D]]-[[Arkansas]]) with 32.18%. Businessman [[Ross Perot]] ([[Independent politician|I]]-Texas) finished in third, with 23.07% of the popular vote.<ref name=results/> Clinton ultimately won the national vote, defeating incumbent President Bush and Perot.<ref>{{cite web|title=1992 Presidential General Election Results|url=http://uselectionatlas.org/RESULTS/national.php?year=1992|publisher=U.S. Election Atlas|accessdate=9 June 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Results==\n{| border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%;\"\n|- style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\"\n! colspan=\"6\" | 1992 United States presidential election in North Dakota<ref name=results>{{cite web|title=1992 Presidential General Election Results - North Dakota|url=http://uselectionatlas.org/RESULTS/state.php?year=1992&fips=38&f=0&off=0&elect=0&minper=0|publisher=U.S. Election Atlas|accessdate=9 June 2012}}</ref>\n|-bgcolor=\"#EEEEEE\" align=\"center\"\n! colspan=\"2\" style=\"width: 15em\" |Party\n! style=\"width: 17em\" |Candidate\n! style=\"width: 5em\" |Votes\n! style=\"width: 7em\" |Percentage\n! style=\"width: 5em\" |Electoral votes\n|-\n! style=\"background-color:#FF3333; width: 3px\" |\n| style=\"width: 130px\" | '''[[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]'''\n| '''[[George H.W. Bush]]''' ([[incumbent]])\n| align=\"right\"